Reviewed lifecycle mapping treats CREATING as
provisioning, UPDATING as updating, ACTIVE and
INACTIVE as success, and DELETING as
terminating; FAILED is terminal and DELETED is
only a delete-confirmation target.
Create, update, and delete responses expose
work-request headers. The runtime resumes
through GetWorkRequest, recovers the affected
ClusterPlacementGroup OCID from work-request
resources when needed, and rereads
GetClusterPlacementGroup before settling.
Pre-create reuse only runs when spec.name and
spec.availabilityDomain are present and keeps
exact compartmentId plus name and
availabilityDomain matching bounded to ACTIVE,
INACTIVE, CREATING, or UPDATING summaries with
matching clusterPlacementGroupType.
Only description, freeformTags, and definedTags
reconcile in place; availabilityDomain,
capabilities, clusterPlacementGroupType,
compartmentId, name, and placementInstruction
remain replacement-only, and the
activate/deactivate/compartment-change helpers
stay out of scope for the published runtime.
Delete keeps the finalizer until the work
request is terminal and GetClusterPlacementGroup
confirms the resource is gone or returns
DELETED.
end note
